M. Vipsanius Agrippa was the great minister of Augustus in war, as Maecenas was in peace: Horace had probably been urged to celebrate his victories‚ and finding the task uncongenial substitutes this dexterous apology.

These lines present a distinct case of the abl. of the personal agent with- out ab. Of.
